    <node id="&#10;Uncas's discovery refers to him finding the two fillies, with their saddles broken and housings soiled, which suggests that they had been running free for several days. This discovery is significant because it indicates that the party has entered enemy territory and their journey must come to an end. Uncas withheld this information for so long according to Duncan because he was silent and reserved, deferring to his father's guidance before speaking up. When he did finally communicate his success in finding the horses, the party was able to assess their situation and take appropriate action." />
