    <node id="&#10;Duncan, the white man, perceives several suspicious and inexplicable movements in the seemingly abandoned Native American village. First, he notices that the rounded roofs of the dwellings are more solidly built than usual, indicating a higher level of industry and foresight. However, the village appears to be deserted, and Duncan grows wary when he sees several human forms approaching him while moving swiftly and silently, dragging what he assumes to be some sort of formidable engine.&#10;&#10;Additionally, Duncan observes a few dark-looking heads emerging from the dwellings, and the place suddenly appears alive with beings that glide from cover to cover so quickly that he cannot examine their intentions or activities. These mysterious movements make Duncan feel alarmed and uneasy, as he is unable to understand what might be happening in this Native American settlement." />
