    <edge source=" Heyward, Chingachgook, Uncas, and the scout were entering the narrows of the lake at dawn, cautiously navigating through numerous little islands while being extra vigilant. They suspected that Montcalm might have left some Indians in ambush along this passage, as it was the road by which Montcalm had retreated with his army. The group was on high alert, looking for any signs of danger and carefully making their way through the intricate channels." target="The Huron's gun fell into the water because, in the confusion and stress of the chase, he was startled by Hawkeye's shot that struck and incapacitated the Huron in the bow of their canoe. This shock caused him to lose his grip on his own gun, and it slipped out of his hands into the lake.&#10;&#10;Chingachgook had a few large drops of blood trickling down his shoulder during the canoe chase because Hawkeye's shot, which hit the Huron in the other canoe, had also grazed Chingachgook's shoulder. Despite this injury, Chingachgook did not make any sound or reveal his pain, as he knew that it was crucial for their survival in such a dangerous moment to remain calm and focused on the task at hand.">
